11 the child advocate or a designee; the commissioner of children and families or a designee; the
12 chief counsel of the committee for public counsel services or a designee; 1 member to be
13 appointed by the committee for public counsel services who shall be an attorney certified by the
14 children and family law division of the committee for public counsel services who shall have a
15 minimum of 7 years of experience in care and protection cases, represents both children and
16 parents and has completed not less than 5 permanent custody or petition-to-dispense trials; 3
17 members appointed by the Massachusetts Bar Association, who shall be former judges who have
