22 have a minimum of 5 years of experience with the advocates, including supervisory experience;
23 1 member appointed by the Massachusetts Alliance of Juvenile Court Clinics who shall be a
24 clinician representative from the court clinic of the juvenile court department; the deputy court
25 administrator for the juvenile court or a designee; 1 member to be appointed by the
26 Massachusetts Commission on LGBTQ Youth; 1 member to be appointed by Jane Doe, Inc.: The
27 Massachusetts Coalition Against Sexual Assault and Domestic Violence; 1 member to be
28 appointed by the Disability Law Center, Inc.; 1 member to be appointed by the Massachusetts
29 Association of Guardians ad Litem; 1 member to be appointed by the Massachusetts Child
30 Welfare Coalition who shall be an attorney; and 1 member to be appointed by the National
31 Association of Counsel for Children. All appointments shall be made not later than 30 days after
32 the effective date of this resolve. Members of the commission shall serve without compensation.
